OL,3,CConsumer confidence rising as summer
OL,4,Choliday season begins
OL,6,FThe survey of 3,000 UK adults, taken
OL,7,Fin early June, found 50% feel able to
OL,8,Fspend freely, although 14% say they
OL,9,Fare still having to actively cut their
OL,10,Fdiscretionary spending to pay for
OL,11,Fessentials, and 3% of are incurring
OL,12,Fdebt to do so.
OL,14,FReflecting on their spending during
OL,15,Fthe last three months compared to the
OL,16,Fprevious quarter, consumers most
OL,17,Fcommonly said they had spent less on
OL,18,Feating out.
