OL,6,FThose saying that the economy is
OL,7,Fgetting worse cite the cost of their
OL,8,Fgroceries (79%), utilities (74%), and
OL,9,Fthe general state of public services
OL,10,Fwhere they live (42%).
OL,12,FLinda Ellett, head of consumer, retail
OL,13,Fand leisure at KPMG UK, said:
OL,14,F"Consumer confidence has rallied over
OL,15,Fthe last quarter and only a fifth of
OL,16,Fconsumers now feel insecure about
OL,17,Ftheir financial circumstance.
